narratives.question_text: Were the resources available to you - library, fabrication labs, classroom, software, desk space, etc. adequate for the fulfillment of the assigned work?  If not, please make suggestions.
comments: While the resources within the library were great for their availability, there was a lack of clarity of which resources should be used when and for what.

He could do a better job, and maybe this is the TA's fault, at making the group assignments more logical in where we should find appropriate references. I don't want it to be spoonfed, but so much of the games are spent figuring out what he actually wants us to do, then when you figure it out, it never is that difficult.
Yes. Didn't need many resources, looks at some of the books in the library reserve shelf and had all the software.
As a non-ARCH student, relied on other ARCH students for access to meeting space. Otherwise, did not utilize resources.
All resources were completely adequate, in every possible way.
Yes, all of the resources I needed were available.
